title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec PLR 22
postcontent:
The PLR-22 pistol is chambered for the popular and economical .22 Long Rifle cartridge (.22LR). It is based on the 5.56mm NATO chambered PLR-16 pistol and shares many parts including the grip and front and rear sights. The PLR-22 is not a simple conversion kit, it is a standalone firearm chambered for the .22LR and is designed for target shooting, plinking, or small game hunting. The PLR-22 and SU-22 operate by blowback action and have a 4140 steel bolt that rides on steel guide rails inside the polymer receiver. The ejector is attached to one of the guide rails and the recoil spring is located above the barrel. The cross-bolt safety and magazine release operate identically to the PLR-16 and SU-16.

Calibers: 	.22LR
Weight unloaded: 	2.8lbs 	1.3kg
Length: 	18.5" 	469.9mm
Barrel length: 	10.1" 	256.5mm
Sight radius: 	12.5" 	317.5mm
Twist: 	1:16"
Capacity: 	26 rounds, Atchison compatible
Trigger pull: 	5.5-7.5 lbs 	24.4-33.4N

The PLR-22 accepts many of the PLR-16 accessories.  It has a threaded muzzle, and tactical suppressors will work very well on the Kel-Tec, greatly reducing the noise signature from the ten inch barrel, and just adding to the overall fun. Weighing just 45 ounces empty, and just about 13 ounces more with the handguards and an empty magazine, the PLR-22 is a handy little weapon, built for fun, but possessing the reliability and accuracy to fill other roles as well, such as hunting or defending the homestead from predators such as foxes and wild dogs. With packs of wild dogs becoming more of a problem each year in wilderness and camping areas, the PLR-22 would prove to be very handy and effective against such threats. While a .22 LR is not the best choice against criminal attacks, the PLR-22 could fill that role as well, unleashing a barrage of lead hollowpoints at one or more attackers, with speed and precision. Whatever the use, the PLR-22 is a dandy little weapon, possessing top-notch accuracy, and providing loads of inexpensive shooting fun. 

Locals may by direct from me.  I must ship to FFL for all others.  Non-locals payment by paypal or money order.  Flat rate shipping of $30.  All Missouri residents pay sales tax in addition to price.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Fabrique National Browning Patent 9mm
location: Surfside Beach, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
Still doing research on this Queen Willameina security force pistol. If you have any info I would appreciate you sharing it with me. It is In great shape for such an old pistol.

Here is some information I found on a blog.

Question:
FN Browning - 1922 - .32 - Blue - 49163 -
Queen Wilhelmina Crown on top of slide and rear of gun under slide 21 on left trigger guard, what looks to be D 7 5 on right of trigger guard...Lion figure(?) above P.V in various locations with letter Y with star above Y located below P.V under Lion figure(?) FN logo on black grips Have documentation of captured enemy equipment from Feb.15,1946(original and duplicate)...wondering age and round about value of gun, slightly worn, no holster

Answer:
The Browning designed, FN Model 1922 was initially produced for the Yugoslavian military. The pistol is an elongated FN Model 1910 with the additional length gained by adding a removal piece to the front of the slide. Model 1922 pistols were used by both military and police and I have not been able to determine if pistols bearing Dutch markings were issued to police departments or military units. (I own serial number 13138, and it is in 380 caliber rather than 32 caliber).

title: For Sale:  Fair priced guns!
postcontent:
ARMSLIST and all other gun marketplaces are community run for the most part. As a gun community we need to come together to rid ourselves of one of the deadliest sins - greed. We are all tired of seeing $500 AK-47s listed at $2000, and $800 fully upgraded AR-15s posted for $4500. Guess what? As gun buyers and members on this and other forums, we are just as responsible for the state of our society as the price gougers and hoarders. We need to come together and do two thing: (1) STOP BUYING AT THESE RIDICULOUS PRICES and (2) click on the ad, go to "Flag" at the top, and press "overpriced." This whole process takes 1.3968 seconds.

These price criminals only have business if someone is ignorant enough to buy and if they spread their advertisement. NOTE TO GUN COMMUNITY: Guns aren't going anywhere. Ammo isn't going anywhere. Magazines are the biggest threat of changing but let's face it, do we really need 100 round drums or is that more of a want? Every time you skip over a $10,000 ad for a $3000 purchased SCAR 17, you have just became part of the problem. Send them a hate email showing the prices before hoarding and then promptly flag their ad so we can get prices back under the 1000s where they all belong. For the uninformed or misinformed audience, I have put together a short list of reasonable prices for standard guns. What I am asking is that everyone read this post and then immediately copy and paste it to another state's listing in the US. Add your own two cents in if you'd like or if I got anything wrong. The regularity will only return if we make it.

AR-15: $600-$1300 depending on brand and usage (shots fired, wear, etc..)
AK-47: $400-$900
SKS:$300-$500
SCAR 16/17: $2000/$2800
AR-10: $1000-1500
Glock: $400-600
10/22: $229
ACR: $2000
1911: $600-1100
9mm ammo: $0.25/round is on the higher end
223/5.56: $0.35/round
.308/7.62 NATO: maybe up to $1/round (on high side)
.22: $0.05/round is high

Again, feel free to add your $0.02, make changes, repost, and then get to the flagging of overpriced scams.

If you dont know how to use a weapon take a class or get rid of it. Stop trying to be gun-ho and buy a assault weapon just to look cool. You guys look like idiots posting a pic of you holding your toy .22 "ar" wearing airsoft gear. If you want to have that image be a man and join the military and stop pretending. If you cant pass the requirements to get in, you shouldnt be owning a gun.
